title: BlackSky buys five Electron launches
summary: BlackSky, one of Rocket Lab’s biggest launch customers, has bought an additional five Electron launches for its next-generation imaging satellites.

title: Cracks in Ancient Martian Mud Surprise NASA's Curiosity Rover Team
summary: A new paper suggests the same conditions that created the cracks could have been favorable to the emergence of microscopic life.

title: Vyoma orders pilot satellites for debris-monitoring constellation
summary: German startup Vyoma has ordered two pilot satellites for its proposed space debris-monitoring constellation from EnduroSat, the eight-year-old Bulgarian cubesat specialist.

title: NASA weighs changes to Artemis 3 if key elements are delayed
summary: NASA has left the door open for changing the scope of Artemis 3, currently set to be the first crewed lunar landing of the program, if key elements suffer major delays.

title: Solestial To Equip Atomos Space Tugs With Solar Arrays
summary: Solar energy startup, Solestial, has unveiled its plans to provide solar arrays for space tugs developed by Denver-based startup Atomos Space.

title: NRO seeks collaboration with industry and academia
summary: The National Reconnaissance Office is looking for partners who are developing advanced technology for satellites and ground systems.

title: KSAT Announces Automated Ka-band Network
summary: Kongsberg Satellite Services (KSAT) has announced an automated Ka-band ground network engineered to serve the evolving needs of small satellite constellations.

title: SDA To Expand North Dakota Satellite Ground Operations
summary: The Space Development Agency (SDA) has revealed intentions to establish a new satellite testing facility at the Grand Forks Air Force Base situated in North Dakota.

title: Starfish Space To Develop Satellite Guidance Software For US Air Force
summary: Starfish Space has secured a $1.8 million investment from the U.S. Air Force's AFWERX technology accelerator to advance its groundbreaking satellite guidance software.
